President John Magufuli, 61, has died of chronic atrial fibrillation,  Vice President Samia Suluhu Hassan announced on Wednesday. The president was admitted at a local hospital in the country's commercial capital Dar es Salaam on March 6, his condition improved and was discharged on March 7. A week later his condition started deteriorating and was rushed back to Mzena hospital where he took his last breath. The Vice President said flags will fly at half mast for 14 days and arrangements for the burial will be communicated. Magufuli who come in power in 2015 he was re-elected for the second and final term in 2020. According to the Vice President Magufuli had been battling atrial fibrillation for over 10 years.